@startuml System Overview
!theme plain
title Autonomous Tool Discovery System - High Level Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam package {
    BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
    BorderColor #333333
}

package "User Interface Layer" {
    [CLI Interface] as CLI
    [REST API] as API
    [Web Dashboard] as Web
}

package "Intent Recognition Layer" {
    [NLP Processor] as NLP
    [Context Manager] as Context
    [Intent Classifier] as Classifier
    
    NLP --> Context : provides context
    Context --> Classifier : enriched features
}

package "Tool Discovery Layer" {
    [Registry Interface] as Registry
    [Capability Matcher] as Matcher
    [Graph Explorer] as Graph
    
    Registry --> Matcher : tool metadata
    Matcher --> Graph : relationships
}

package "Tool Selection & Learning Layer" {
    [Q-Learning Engine] as QLearning
    [Epsilon Greedy Selector] as Selector
    [Combination Scorer] as Scorer
    
    QLearning --> Selector : Q-values
    Selector --> Scorer : candidates
}

package "Execution & Monitoring Layer" {
    [MCP Connection Manager] as MCP
    [Parallel Executor] as Executor
    [Performance Monitor] as Monitor
    
    MCP --> Executor : connections
    Executor --> Monitor : metrics
}

package "Learning & Adaptation Layer" {
    [Pattern Miner] as Miner
    [Feedback Processor] as Feedback
    [Model Adapter] as Adapter
    
    Miner --> Feedback : patterns
    Feedback --> Adapter : updates
}

' Layer connections
CLI --> NLP : user query
API --> NLP : user query
Web --> NLP : user query

Classifier --> Registry : intent vector
Graph --> QLearning : tool candidates
Scorer --> MCP : selected tools
Monitor --> Miner : execution data
Adapter --> QLearning : model updates

' External systems
database "Tool Registry\nDatabase" as DB
database "Q-Learning\nStorage" as QDB
cloud "MCP Servers" as MCPServers {
    [Filesystem MCP]
    [SQLite MCP]
    [Search MCP]
    [Custom MCPs]
}

Registry --> DB : queries
QLearning --> QDB : read/write
MCP --> MCPServers : JSON-RPC

note bottom of MCPServers
    External tool servers
    communicating via
    Model Context Protocol
end note

@enduml